    },
    {
      "id": "130a7369876ac3860c1bcccbf2d4f015dc09acb3",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2013-11-27 22:14:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nThe right thing here may be to use LO_FLAGS_AUTOCLEAR (see http://lxr.free-electrons.com/source/drivers/block/loop.c#L1011) but that will require using ioctl() rather than system(\"losetup -d ...\"). \n\nMoreover, in newer kernels calling the detach ioctl on a loop device will with reference count greater than 1 will set the autoclear flag and return 0. This may confuse a second 'losetup -d' invocation which finds the device already detached. This is all just terrible.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
